	   <tr><td colspan=2>Considering the hp-pool and amount of strength a troll or ogre has, i dont think they would want to cast fear 5 times.&nbsp;&nbsp;Half as much would be sufficient.  Considering Stamina and Strength are both about 120 for both large races, this gives them quite an advantage meleeing, especially after level 20 when str becomes a major factor in hitting after the damage cap is gone.  Trolls also get regeneration, which in addition is another great recovery tactic.  Ogres cannot be stunned from frontal regular melee attacks, which means they dont have to worry about being stunned when attacking or casting as much.  Both can wear heavy plate armor without being encumbered as easily, thus giving higher ac.<br><br>Considering the Dex-agility is lower for big slow ogres and trolls, that also lowers the ac, and special defenses like parry, dodge, riposte.  Not that erudites are exactly speed demons but that does give the smaller race one small stat advantage.  This is of course balanced by equipment<br><br>In any case, this applies to fear kiting in that the smaller races, while having larger mana pools and usually better special defenses will find fear kiting much more effective than larger races which will be able to melee their way out of a fight better.<br>&nbsp;<br>20th Level Inky Shadowknight on Cazic-Thule server.</td></tr>
